{{Quote|What ''is'' a three-fingered shenbit wrangler, anyway?''"<br />"''Seven fingers too slow.|[[Taryn Zel]] and [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]|<ref name="Fate of the Jedi: Apocalypse">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Apocalypse]]''</ref>}}
The '''shenbit bonecrusher''' was a large carnivorous lizard native to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Barab I/Legends|Barab I]]. It was covered with bony and thorny plates. It also had two horns and a long tail.

[[Barabel/Legends|Barabels]] hunted bonecrushers for sport and meat. Although the shenbit was extremely dangerous to most humanoid species of the galaxy, it was considered to be fairly average prey among the Barabels. In fact, in the [[Barabel (language)|Barabel]], "shenbit" roughly translated to "weak person" in [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Galactic Basic Standard]].

The ''[[Braxant Bonecrusher]]'' and the [[shenbit bonecrusher blow]] were named after the species.

[[Saba Sebatyne]] often referred to shenbits while making comparisons and examples.

